articular advertisements (which quickly respond to linguistic change). Naturally, the book presents the characteristics of the digital language variety (and coins the term digilect) but only to give a framework to the impact analysis. It is important to document changes in progress and thus direct attention to potential outcomes. The current linguistic change is different from previous ones primarily in its speed and form of spreading, and it not only brings innovative grammatical forms and writing/spelling solutions but may also have far-reaching cultural and educational consequences in the long run.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aCommunication and technology. 0aDigital communications. 0aLanguage and languagesxComputer network resources. 4aDigital. 4aInternet. 4aSprachvariante. 4aVariety. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104971370 cprintz978311049990240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110499117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110499117.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LB  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2017